        Official Singles Chart on 8/5/2020

        8 May 2020 - 14 May 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Keeping the review fairly brief tonight because of the bank holiday…

        Firstly, Drake’s got his sixth #1 & look, this is going to be one of those songs which will be fine to see less than a month at the top, but it’ll be really tiring if it stays there any longer! I certainly see ‘Toosie Slide’ having more longevity on the singles chart than ‘Dark Lane Demo Tapes’ will on the albums chart. As for the song, eh, it’s probably still a light 6/10 for me.

        Now, what I’m a lot more excited about are the two big remixes that came out last week! As you all know by now, I adore the original version of ‘Say So’ thanks to its general 80s disco feel & sensual delivery from Doja Cat, but while there are some questionable lines from Nicki Minaj in her remix, she still brings enough of an entertaining presence to the remix to make that almost just as good. Man, I really hope this becomes a future #1, then 2020 would really be set to be an amazing year for the charts!

        The other is ‘Savage’ & while I’m a little bit less impressed by Beyonce’s additional verse in this remix, her rapping is still better than previous times she’s tried to do it in my opinion! Then again, for as much as I would call Beyonce a legend at this point, Megan Thee Stallions’ part still stands out for me just because of the sheer swagger & attitude she’s bringing to the table.

        Not really anything of note to say about any of the debuts sadly, except AJ Tracey’ a lot harder than expected! I also really like the gains for: ‘Rockstar’ (peaked higher in the UK than in the US!), ‘Rover’ & ‘If The World Was Ending’. Meanwhile, the re-entry for ‘Sicko Mode’ is okay & ‘Don’t Rush’ returning is amazing. Both came back for very different reasons & a while after they first charted, but I don’t see either of them surpassing the success of their initial chart run!

        Sadly, there were also a lot of disappointments this week! Now, a lot of that blame can be placed on OCC because of their ridiculous ACR rule, which caused a lot of incredible hits to plummet, including: ‘Blinding Lights’, ‘Roses’, ‘Don’t Start Now’, ‘Physical’ & ‘Lonely’... yeah, they might’ve done really well over these past few weeks, but my point remains, ACR is a problem here because there are songs above it in the current chart that are receiving lower overall chart sales. As I’ve mentioned before, it doesn’t reflect the true popularity of these hits! We all knew it was coming, but I’m still very disappointed.

        What the public can be blamed for is causing the huge talent of ‘If You’re Too Shy [Let Me Know]’ to fall a massive 23 places & not letting ‘Be Kind’ land a Top 40 debut!

        Oh well, I’ve had a lot of positive things to say lately, shame this week was just okay at best.

        Anyway, enjoy the bank holiday weekend everybody! :)

        J

        Jamie
